6: Get up, Lilith. Come with me!
10:
What is it this time, Estariel? 
I'm in the middle of work—
14:
How many times have I told you?
Call me Estel. Now come. I take
precedence over silly slips of paper,
don't I?
18:
These slips of paper are quite
important, thank you very much!
And I have a lot to catch up on
every day—
21:
You aren't suited for this type of
work. Stop wasting your time, and
leave it to someone else.
38:
Wh-what are we doing here? Where
even are we?
53: A-are you sure you don't want to...
62: To Nexus, the birthplace of androids!
67:
Fascinating. It is a beautiful
structure.
70:
The technology of another world... 
It is quite remarkable.
75:
This is Nexus—the place where
androids go to decide their future.
80: Are you not allowed to come in here?
84:
It's not that, it's just... kind of
embarrassing...
88:
This is usually a place where people
come to propose to their significant
other, and such...
96:
If that's the case, then why did you
want to come here so badly, Estel?
102:
Androids and elves are alike, are
they not?
105:
Born from a fervent wish—us, to
celebrate love and light for eternity...
114:
I can appreciate the impulse behind
our creation, even if we're trying to
evolve past our original purpose.
121:
Is this why you came here? To learn
more about yourself...
129:
The techniques that created us
elves are lost. But the technology
that created androids still remains.
131:
Using that technology, I could
create a new race of people,
couldn't I?
139:
Doesn't the possibility excite you?
I'm eager to try my hand at it.
152:
Why not? I don't intend to sacrifice
other lives in the process. If worse
comes to worst, then I will be the
only one to suffer the consequences.
157:
Are you listening to yourself right
now?!
163: Alk, this person is as crazy as Regis!
168:
How boring... And here I thought this
would be the best way to facilitate
evolution...
173: Do you wish for change that badly?
176: If so, then I know of a method.
183:
Blood-red pancakes topped with
liquid acid and tapioca pearls.
188:
Is this what passes for street food in
Palpebra nowadays?!
191:
Anyone who finishes a plate is
awarded prize money.
196:
Should this... truly be ingested
through the mouth?
201:
The sign for the pancakes claimed
that you would discover a new side
to yourself by eating this.
205:
I see. In that case, I must see this
through.
221:
That was... child's play... Nothing to
fear...
224: Estel, there are tears in your eyes.
238:
Amusing, is it? Let's see if you're still
laughing after you have a bite. Dig
in!
247:
Don't be shy. Enjoy the meal and
stay for some conversation, my
friends!
